%I A395988 #10 May 13 2026 12:12:23
%S A395988 10,18,28,40,54,70,88,108,130,154,180,210,247,283
%N A395988 Minimum transmission of a connected quartic graph on n vertices.
%C A395988 Here, transmission means the Wiener index, the sum of distances between all unordered pairs of vertices.
%C A395988 The terms a(6)-a(17) are the entries in the w_{n,4} row of Table 2 of Knor, Škrekovski, and Tepeh (2019).
%H A395988 M. Knor, R. Škrekovski and A. Tepeh, <a href="https://match.pmf.kg.ac.rs/electronic_versions/Match81/n1/match81n1_119-132.pdf">Chemical Graphs with the Minimum Value of Wiener Index</a>,  MATCH Commun. Math. Comput. Chem. 81 (2019), 119-132.
%H A395988 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/notebooks/GraphTheory/Transmission-MinimalRegularGraph.nb">Transmission-Minimal Regular Graph</a>.
%e A395988 a(5) = 10, attained by the complete graph K_5.
%e A395988 a(6) = 18, attained by the octahedral graph.
%Y A395988 Cf. A395986 (minimal transmission for cubic graphs).
%Y A395988 Cf. A395987 (number of transmission-minimal cubic graphs).
%Y A395988 Cf. A395989 (number of transmission-minimal quartic graphs).
%K A395988 nonn,more,new
%O A395988 5,1
